Class BitSetUtil

java.lang.Object
  jeva.util.BitSetUtil

public class BitSetUtil
extends java.lang.Object

This utility class contains functions to encode int or double values in a BitSet.

Extracts an integer value from the given BitSet from offset of the given amount of bits (given by lenght).

Parameters:
bitSet - the bit set to operate on
offset - the offset in the bit set
length - the length of the bit string that represents the encoded int
Returns:
the extracted integer value
Throws:
java.lang.RuntimeException - if length is greater than the bit-count of int

Encodes the given integer value in the BitSet from the position offset by the given amount of bits.

Parameters:
bitSet - the BitSet to operate on
offset - the offset in the bit set
length - the length of the bit string that should represent the given value
value - the value to encode in the bit set
Returns:
the modified bit set
Throws:
java.lang.RuntimeException - if length is greater than the amount of bits in an integer value
java.lang.RuntimeException - if value is greather than the value encodeable by the given amount of bits or if value == Integer.MIN_VALUE (no absolute value awailable as int)

doubleToBitSet

public static java.util.BitSet doubleToBitSet(java.util.BitSet bitSet,
                                              int offset,
                                              int length,
                                              double minValue,
                                              double maxValue,
                                              double value)
Encodes a double value in a BitSet by scaling the interval (given by minValue and maxValue) to the co-domain of the natual number representable by n bits (n=lenght). minValue and maxValue are necessary to calculate a scaling function between the two co-domains.

Parameters:
bitSet - the BitSet to operate on
offset - the offset in the given bit set
length - the number of bits used to encode value
minValue - minimal value of value
maxValue - maximal value of value
value - the value to encode
Returns:
the manipulated bit set
Throws:
java.lang.RuntimeException - if the value of value does not fit in ]minValue, maxValue[
java.lang.RuntimeException - if the number of bits (length) is bigger than Long.SIZE
